..TEXT:
|l'uno a l'altro chini~: The posture of the two blind
souls, leaning one to the other in intimate conversation, as if Dante
were farther away from them than he is, continues to bring out the
psychological distance and isolation of blindness which was expressed
by the opening "costui."  See n. to vs.  1.
