..TEXT:
|fer~ = ^fecero.~  |supini~: The souls are seated, and
Dante is standing, hence it would be natural for them to turn
their faces "supine" to him; but the gesture is characteristic of
the blind, and for any reader who has observed this it serves to
evoke the image of the two figures most vividly, putting the
focus of the poem on the sightless eyes in the upturned faces.
