..TEXT:
|O anima~: The souls address Dante as a "soul," even
though they know that he is here in his body (as is immediately
recognized in the words which follow).  |fitta~: Past participle
of ^figgere~, "to plant."  Cf. ^Inf.~ XIX, 50.
