|tanto maravigliar de la tua grazia~: See vss. 79-80
and ^Purg.~ XIII, 145-46.  |la tua grazia~: The God-given grace
that makes possible this extraordinary journey, which has caused
great marvel before (^Purg.~ VIII, 65-66).
