..TEXT:
|Per mezza Toscana... persona~: In reply to the
question "onde vieni" Dante brings in the course of the river Arno,
from the river's source to the city of Florence, which "sits" on its
banks.  Compare Francesca's identification of herself in a similar way
in ^Inf.~ V, 97-98, Virgil's discourse on the origin of Mantua in
^Inf.~ XX, 61-81, and Dante's identification of himself in ^Inf.~
XXIII, 94-95.  Guido del Duca, who will be named in vs.  81, then
traces the whole course of the river.
..TCHR:
484
