..TEXT:
|per ristoro... loro~: The heavens (^il ciel~),
by the heat of the sun, cause the water of the sea to evaporate
and rise; this then falls as rain to replenish the rivers with
water ("ci@o che va con loro"), and the rivers in turn, with the
water they bring to the sea, replace that which was lost through
evaporation.
