..TEXT:
|Circe~: The enchantress Circe, daughter of Helios,
god of the Sun, and Perse.  She dwelt in the island of Aeaea (in
Virgil's time, Circaeum Promontorium; modern Mount Circeo), on
the north side of the Gulf of Gaeta, upon which Ulysses was cast
(see Homer, ^Odyssey~ X, 133-50), and she had the power of
transforming men into beasts.
..TCHR:
