..TEXT:
|poscia li ancide come antica belva~: Then, after
selling them alive, Fulcieri slaughters them like old cattle,
i.e., like an ox too old to work, which is sold to the butcher.
Del Lungo comments: " 'Belva' @e qui, poeticamente, nel
significato generico che ha, di 'animale grosso' (distintamente
da quello di 'bestia feroce')."  ("Here 'beast' is used
poetically in its general significance of large animal, rather
than ferocious animal.")
