..TEXT:
|Rinier~: Rinieri de' Paolucci da Calboli
(pronounced C@alboli), member of an illustrious Guelph family of
Forl@i, was born probably at the beginning of the thirteenth
century and was ^podest@a~ of Faenza in 1247, of Parma in 1252,
and of Ravenna in 1265 (the year of Dante's birth).  For a full
account of his very active political life and his many exploits,
see P. Toynbee (1968), pp. 543-44.
..TCHR:
