..TEXT:
|del ben richesto al vero e al trastullo~: Connects
with "brullo" in vs. 91.  This "good" is virtue in general or
those virtues required in the serious business of life and in
courtly pastimes.  Cf. the French ^agr$ements.~  |Cortesia~ in a
broad sense means good manners and a gay life.
