..TEXT:
|Bretinoro~: Now Bertinoro, small town in Romagna,
between Forl@i and Cesena.  After being for a time under the
lordship of the Malatesta of Rimini, the town passed toward the
end of the thirteenth century into the hands of the Ordelaffi of
Forl@i, in whose possession it was at the date of the journey.
According to the ^Ottimo Commento~, whose account is repeated by
Benvenuto, it was in its best days renowned for the hospitality
of its nobles.
