|'l demonio lor~: Maghinardo (or Mainardo)
Pagano da Susinana, head of the Pagani family in Dante's time,
was lord of Faenza in 1290, of Forl@i in 1291, and of Imola in
1296.  He is mentioned by Guido da Montefeltro in ^Inf.~ XXVII,
50, as "il lioncel dal nido bianco," a reference to his arms (see
n. to ^Inf.~ XXVII, 50), and was commonly called "the Demon."  He
died in Imola in 1302.  For further particulars, see P. Toynbee
(1968), pp. 409-10.
..TCHR:
