|tralignando~: The term continues the metaphor of
plant stock that degenerates.  See Butler, who provides the
following quotation from the Italian version of Crescentius,
where the term is used of the apple: "Invecchia tosto, e nella
sua vecchiezza traligna."  ("It gets old fast and in old age
degenerates.")
