|Anciderammi~ = ^mi uccider@a.~  |Anciderammi qualunque
m'apprende~: These are the words of Cain, speaking to the Lord
after he had slain his brother Abel.  See Gen. 4:13-14:
"Dixitque Cain ad Dominum: Maior est iniquitas mea, quam ut
veniam merear.  Ecce eiicis me hodie a facie terrae, et a facie
tua.  Abscondar et ero vagus et profugus in terra; omnis igitur
qui invenerit me occidet me."  ("Cain said to the Lord, 'My
punishment is too great to bear.  You are driving me today from
the soil; and from your face I shall be hidden.  And I shall be a
fugitive and a wanderer on the earth, and whoever finds me will
kill me.'")
