..TEXT:
|camo~: Cf. ^freno~ in ^Purg.~ XIII, 40.  See Ps.
31[32]:9: "In camo et freno maxillas eorum constringe, qui non
approximant ad te."  ("With bit and bridle their temper must be
curbed, else they will not come near you.")  Also see Dante, ^De
mon.~ III, xvi, 9.
